				<p>My dad was the pudding maker in our family, and the recipe you gave is very similar&#8211;only we used (and still do), whole eggs&#8211;just beat them up really good.  Mom had a flat Tupperware sheet cake kind of container that she made hers in when i was a teenager.  I&#8217;ve had it since she passed away in 1994, and that is what I make my banana pudding in.  Good ole Tupperware container is probably about 38 years old&#8211;and still going strong!</p>
