				<p>I had been craving banana pudding for a while and knew one person that made great banana pudding but didn&#8217;t measure anything therefore could not tell me (a beginner) how to make it.  I searched high and low for a recipe that did not use box pudding (I grew up on REAL BANANA PUDDING). Finally, I found this recipe and I must say it is absolutely perfect and just what I remember having when I was little. I always thought  it would be so hard to make but the directions are great and it is so easy.  The only thing I found is that I have to double the recipe to have enough pudding for the wafers to soak up.  I love this recipe and I thank you so much for sharing it!</p>
				
