				<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
					<a href="http://www.southernplate.com/2008/07/homemade-banana-pudding-tutorial.html/comment-page-3#comment-275733">
					March 2, 2011 - 10:55 am</a>				</div>
				
				
				<p>Nilla wafers are required for banana pudding. I use store brands for most things but I&#8217;m stuck on Nillas for this. Not only do they taste better but they look prettier. Many store brand  vanilla wafers are yellow, instead of white, inside and don&#8217;t look so good when you cut through them during serving. Love REAL banana pudding. Single women, it&#8217;s a good way to get a man!</p>
				
